<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="897" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d897">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 850a.001/6.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 23.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch No. 6
                            Luxemburg series of the 4th ultimo, transmitting a letter from Her Royal
                            Highness Marie Anne, Regent of the Grand Duchy of Luxemburg, in which
                            she notifies the President of the death of His Royal Highness the Grand
                            Duke William and that the Regency will be continued until the attainment
                            of majority of Her Royal Highness Marie Adelaide, I inclose, with office
                            copy, a letter addressed by the President to Her Royal Highness Marie
                            Anne, acknowledging her letter.<note n="1" xml:id="d897fn1">Not
                                printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>You will forward the copy to the Foreign Office of Luxemburg and deliver
                            the original in the manner most agreeable to Her Royal Highness.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>